<figureCitation box="[356,487,1929,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–58" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1859,1881]" captionTargetBox="[251,1332,213,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-63@35.[226,1360,193,1837]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 54–58. Beardius dioi sp. n., male. 54—wing; 55—thorax; 56—hypopygium, lateral view; 57—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 58—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270920/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 56–58</figureCitation>
